                    <h3>Witches Abroad, Terry Pratchett</h3>
                    <p>To begin with, Terry Pratchett is a great author. I've read most of his recent books, and a few of the older (published in the 80's) books. They are all good. Deep, funny adventures that make fun of everything at some point. This is just the one I'm currently reading. An old witch dies and leaves her position as fairy godmother to three other witches.  </p>
