                    <a href="http://www.us.penguingroup.com/static/packages/us/yreaders/savvy/extras.php"><img id="textcontent" style="float:left" src="http://www.us.penguingroup.com/static/packages/us/yreaders/savvy/im/savvy_wallpaper_01_small.jpg"/></a>
                    <h3>Savvy, Ingrid Law</h3>
                    <p>A story about a family of superpowered average people. They don't save the world, but they survive it with such crazy gifts as sneezing backwards in time, getting people to believe anything you write. A lovely pair of books about family, growing-up, and finding your place.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row-fluid" id="textcontent">
                    <a href="http://browse.deviantart.com/art/Holes-Book-Cover-54547907"><img id="textcontent" style="float:left" src="http://th03.deviantart.net/fs18/200H/f/2007/123/5/c/Holes___Book_Cover_Design_by_Keriberrygirl.jpg"/></a>
                    <h3>Holes, Louis Sachar</h3>
                    <p>A story with many stories in it, everything falls into place at the end, and everything is perfectly timed. A boy is falsely convicted and sent to a detention center in a desert, where he finds the beginning and ending of the legend of his family's curse, the great bandit Kissin' Kate, and the rainless Camp Green Lake.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row-fluid" id="textcontent">
